              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/25930446/" class="">第44页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/49542325/" class=" " title="埃里克·布莱尔">埃里克·布莱尔</a>
                (bu)
              
                <span class="allstar40" title="推荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="25930446">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">The essence of modernity lay in the development of this new sentiment of individuality: the disposition increasingly to guide one's life by one's own talents and inclinations rather than to fill the place into which one had been born. </span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2013-04-22 16:30</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>The essence of modernity lay in the development of this new sentiment of individuality: the disposition increasingly to guide one's life by one's own talents and inclinations rather than to fill the place into which one had been born. </q></blockquote>
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







