        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/28779677/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/28779677/" class="">专制与政治对立</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/Akmus1993/" class=" " title="Akmus">Akmus</a>
              
                <span class="allstar40" title="推荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="28779677">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">One widely recognized clue is the current state of the distinction between private life and public world. The private world is that of the family, and of individual conscience as each individual makes his or her own choice of beliefs and interests. Such a private life would not be possible witout the overarching public world of the state, which sustains a structure of law appropriate to a self-det...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2013-10-01 01:51</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>One widely recognized clue is the current state of the distinction between private life and public world. The private world is that of the family, and of individual conscience as each individual makes his or her own choice of beliefs and interests. Such a private life would not be possible witout the overarching public world of the state, which sustains a structure of law appropriate to a self-determining association. Politics only survives so long as this overarching structure of public law recognizes its own limits. As Pericles put it in his famous funeral oration free and tolerant in our private lives; but in public affairs we keep to the law.’ The actual boundary, both in law and in people’s attitudes, between what is public and what is private is, of course, constantly changing. Homosexuality and religion, which used to be publicly regulated, are now largely private, while rape within marriage and abuse of children are increasingly subject to law. It is the fact of recognizing such a division which distinguishes politics – we may loosely identify it with freedom and democracy- from despotism.</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div> It is the fact of recognizing such a division which distinguishes politics – we may loosely identify it with freedom and democracy- from despotism.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>真的只要有了这种认识就够了吗？相比government与citizen之间的矛盾，作者对人与人之间的矛盾和纷争真是太傻太天真了。同样的，在本书最后一章作者所不屑的道德代替政治，也绝对不是在政府与公民这对范畴里就说得清楚的，其解决方法，也绝对不是收紧政治活动、限制公共权力这么简单，自由意志主义的天真真的不用再赘述了。如果我们要再考察，那就要回到政治出现之前的那个混沌时代，那时候，政治还酝酿于简单的社会互动之中，在这些互动之中，蕴藏着人与人之间冲突与纠纷的本质，它在我们所处的历史阶段被政治所调节着，但终有一天，政治不再控制得住。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>这绝对不是社会进化论或者追寻某种规律的历史学。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>这是我们所看到的。
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







