        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/28779586/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/28779586/" class="">专制与政治对立</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/Akmus1993/" class=" " title="Akmus">Akmus</a>
              
                <span class="allstar40" title="推荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="28779586">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">Above all, the name of politics itself. When concepts are stretched too far, they snap and lose their usefulness. â&euro;&oelig;Politcsâ&euro;? used to refer merely to the actions aof monarchs, parliaments. And ministers, and to the activities of the politically committed who helped or hindered their accession to authority. Everything else was social or private life. With the expansion of the power of governments, ...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2013-10-01 01:43</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>Above all, the name of politics itself. When concepts are stretched too far, they snap and lose their usefulness. “Politcs” used to refer merely to the actions aof monarchs, parliaments. And ministers, and to the activities of the politically committed who helped or hindered their accession to authority. Everything else was social or private life. With the expansion of the power of governments, nearly everything has come to be described, in one way, or another, as ‘political’. We may mention here just one fo the many reasons for this. Governments wishing to claim credit for all good things, and oppositions wishing to dispense blame for all bad things, have colluded in spreading the idea that all things, good and bad, are caused by political policies. This idea can turn subjects into petitioners of government, from which all benefits seem to flow, and that in turn reinforces the idea that everything actually is political.</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>喜欢作者的这种思路，通过对“政治”这一概念的收紧，也引发了我们对政治活动边界的思考，这或许正是这本书中文翻译名的苦衷吧——对“政治”的一种收紧，其实就是对政府行为，对公共权力的一种收紧，这对当代中国太具有通识意义了。 而且还有对公共生活和私人生活这对两分的阐述，对政治侵入生活，政治成为生活，政治剥夺生活的批判。。。作者真的不是在针对某国的某几十年吗？
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







<div class="rec-sec">

    <span class="rec">

<a href="https://www.douban.com/accounts/register?reason=collect" class="j a_show_login lnk-sharing lnk-douban-sharing">推荐</a>
